Items.description: — The Pittsburgh Steelers followed a stumbling first half with a strong final 30 minutes to beat the Dallas Cowboys 16-3 on Thursday night in the first NFL preseason game in two years.
— Dwayne Haskins got advice from his QB coach to play like a jazz player.

— Rookie running back Rhamondre Stevenson had two touchdown runs, including a 91-yard score with just over a minute to play to help the New England Patriots beat Washington 22-13 to open the exhibition season for both teams Thursday night.
— Following his first look at his offense in a game situation, the best news for Atlanta first-year coach Arthur Smith was the dismal results didn't count.

— Rookie Zaven Collins looked comfortable as Arizona's middle linebacker, Matt Prater booted game-tying and game-winning field goals, and the Cardinals rallied for a 19-16 victory over the Dallas Cowboys in a preseason game on Friday night.
— Once rookie quarterback Justin Fields settled in the Chicago Bears saw the playmaking ability they dreamed about on draft day.
— Neither Drew Lock nor Teddy Bridgewater stood out from the other as both of Denver's quarterback candidates faced Minnesota backups.
— Trevor Lawrence’s professional debut opened with a sack and a fumble, hardly ideal but not overly concerning for the Jacksonville Jaguars.

— Tyler Huntley ran for a 7-yard touchdown with 6:35 remaining, and the Baltimore Ravens extended their preseason winning streak to 18 games with a 17-14 victory over the New Orleans Saints on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Ravens vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: — Three points, two drives and one solid debut for Zach Wilson.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. New York Jets

Items.description: — A little over six months after becoming the first team to win a Super Bowl played on its homefield, the Tampa Bay Buccaneers were excited about finally being back in Raymond James Stadium.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description: — Green Bay Packers quarterback Jordan Love's pro debut ended earlier than expected.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Houston Texans

Items.description: — With one deep strike, Trey Lance showed why the San Francisco 49ers invested so heavily to draft him this offseason. With a few shakier moments in his preseason debut, Lance showed why the Niners aren't rushing to make him their starter.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: — With Derek Carr skipping Las Vegas' preseason opener and Marcus Mariota nursing a leg injury, third-string quarterback Nathan Peterman stepped on the field Saturday night against the Seattle Seahawks with a chip on his shoulder.
Items.vs: Las Vegas Raiders vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description: — Nearly 70,000 football fans filled up the terraces, concourses and party areas for the first time at SoFi Stadium, reveling in the opportunity to see Los Angeles' two hometown teams in person at their new address.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Rams vs. Los Angeles Chargers

Items.description: — Jacob Eason was efficient in place of the injured Carson Wentz, and rookie Sam Ehlinger delivered in the final quarter for the Indianapolis Colts.

— Cam Newton resumed his habit of tossing the ball to fans after New England scored touchdowns. It's his way of showing appreciation to fans, especially after a season where most were forced to stay home.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: — Rookie running back Jaret Patterson did a little bit of everything and scored the go-ahead touchdown in the fourth quarter in Washington’s 17-13 preseason victory over the Cincinnati Bengals on Friday night.

— Patrick Mahomes was pretty good, backups Chad Henne and Shane Buechele were even better, and the Kansas City Chiefs won their second straight preseason game by beating the Arizona Cardinals 17-10 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: — Even if it was a preseason game, Buffalo quarterback Mitchell Trubisky gained possibly a small measure of satisfaction at Soldier Field on Saturday.
— Zach Wilson provided the New York Jets more reason for optimism while picking apart a Green Bay Packers defense resting nearly all of its starters.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. New York Jets

Items.description: — Many of the Baltimore Ravens players weren't aware they'd made NFL history until coach John Harbaugh walked into the locker room after Saturday night's 20-3 win over the Carolina Panthers and told them.
— The Miami Dolphins had an early injury scare to one of their new additions, then soundly defeated an opponent they became familiar with this week.
— Pittsburgh Steelers quarterback Ben Roethlisberger enjoyed a perfect preseason debut.

— Briean Boddy-Calhoun returned a fumble 42 yards for a touchdown and the Tennessee Titans beat the Super Bowl champion Tampa Bay Buccaneers, who played without Tom Brady and several starters, 34-3 in a preseason game Saturday night.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description: — The Indianapolis Colts will pick a No. 2 quarterback between Jacob Eason and Sam Ehlinger, with the strong possibility they'll also be choosing a fill-in starter until Carson Wentz is ready to return.
— Cooper Rush's days as the backup to Dak Prescott in Dallas might not be over.

Items.vs: Los Angeles Rams vs. Las Vegas Raiders

Items.description: — Teddy Bridgewater is trying not to get caught up or focus on being in the middle of the Denver Broncos' quarterback competition.
— Case Keenum and KhaDarel Hodge spend a lot of time practicing together and have developed chemistry.
Items.vs: Cleveland Browns vs. New York Giants

Items.description: — Trey Lance's bid to be the San Francisco 49ers' starting quarterback was a bit of a rollercoaster Sunday night, but the rookie rebounded from a rough start to keep his hopes alive.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Chargers vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: — Jameis Winston picked opportune moments to let it fly in first NFL start since 2019.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Jacksonville Jaguars

Items.description: — The Indianapolis Colts' depth chart at quarterback took another hit.
— The ball left James Morgan's right hand, zipped through the thick MetLife Stadium air and somehow landed in Kenny Yeboah's hands for a touchdown as time expired.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description: — Sam Darnold felt the Carolina Panthers needed a night like this before the regular season.
— Patrick Mahomes and Tyreek Hill have talked openly about the Kansas City Chiefs chasing a perfect season.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Minnesota Vikings

Items.description: — Josh Allen had the Buffalo Bills’ up-tempo passing attack humming so efficiently in his preseason debut receiver Emmanuel Sanders wondered when his turn would come to make a play.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: — J.K. Dobbins going down with an injury overshadowed the Baltimore Ravens making a little preseason history.
— After seven Super Bowl wins and more than two decades in the NFL, Tom Brady remains a student of the game.
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: — A trio of Broncos returning from injuries celebrated their 2021 debuts in Denver's 17-12 win over the Los Angeles Rams' reserves in the preseason finale Saturday night.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Los Angeles Rams

Items.description: — With most of Seattle's stars serving as spectators for the preseason, Pete Carroll finally saw the Seahawks' depth perform in dominating fashion.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. Los Angeles Chargers

Items.description: — Trevor Lawrence took the reps coach Urban Meyer said he needed, and now has a taste of success going into the regular season.

— Nine months after tearing both the ACL and MCL in his left knee, Bengals quarterback Joe Burrow took his first snaps Sunday against the Miami Dolphins, who rallied to win 29-26 in a wild preseason finale for both teams.
— The San Francisco 49ers got a chance to show off their quarterback platoon before the regular season.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. Las Vegas Raiders

Items.description: — Mac Jones is really pushing Cam Newton for the New England Patriots' starting job at quarterback.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: — Baker Mayfield finally got a chance to play in the preseason.
— Tom Brady and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers didn't flinch.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: — The Minnesota Vikings overcame a choppy start to storm back and tie the game after regulation against the Cincinnati Bengals.
— With new coach Urban Meyer’s championship college resume and No. 1 overall pick Trevor Lawrence leading the offense, the Jacksonville Jaguars were supposed to be much-improved this season.
— The start of a new era couldn't have gone much better for the Philadelphia Eagles.
— If beating the team that traded him gave Sam Darnold any vindication, the fourth-year quarterback certainly wasn't sharing it.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. New York Jets

Items.description: — Knowing it was going to take the Steelers' new-look offense time to find its footing, Ben Roethlisberger was counting on Pittsburgh’s defense to keep the score close.
— Brandon Staley and Justin Herbert shared a smile and shook hands outside the locker room before the new Los Angeles Chargers coach congratulated the second-year quarterback on a job well done.
— Nick Bosa was ready to kick back and relax while the San Francisco 49ers coasted to a season-opening victory.
— Russell Wilson looked right at home in Seattle's new offense.

— Kylar Murray provided a dazzling hint of how much better he might be in his third NFL season. Chandler Jones made it very clear why the Arizona Cardinals need to sign him to the new contract he wants — and soon.

— Every time the Kansas City Chiefs needed a big play on Sunday, their magician under center produced the kind of mesmerizing moment that left the Cleveland Browns shaking their heads in awe and frustration.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Cleveland Browns

Items.description: — For the first time since Peyton Manning retired after winning Super Bowl 50, the Denver Broncos may have a quarterback. All it took was 11 tries.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: — Xavien Howard was one of the NFL’s best players at causing turnovers in 2020. He was back at it Sunday to help the Dolphins preserve a victory to open this season.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: — Jameis Winston and the hurricane-displaced Saints looked right at home in northeast Florida — no doubt to the delight of fans rebuilding homes and lives back in New Orleans.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: — Matthew Stafford's second pass for the Los Angeles Rams traveled 53 majestic yards through the air and dropped right into the hands of Van Jefferson, who fell down untouched, stood up and scored.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Rams vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: — After a premature bench-clearing celebration and a couple of blunders that almost cost the Raiders the game, the party could finally begin for real after the first game with fans in Las Vegas.
Items.vs: Las Vegas Raiders vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: — Taylor Heinicke and Dustin Hopkins made the most of their second chances.
— Jon Gruden's long, arduous multi-state, multi-year rebuilding project may finally be nearing its end.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Las Vegas Raiders

Items.description: — Mac Jones kept his mistakes to a minimum, moved the ball down the field and did enough to earn his first NFL victory with the New England Patriots.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: — Justin Fields got his first extended look as a pro. And it might be a long-term arrangement.
— Baker Mayfield wasn't missing a snap. So once his left shoulder got popped back into its socket, there was no stopping him.
— Courtland Sutton re-established himself as Denver's go-to guy with a career day.
— Jimmy Garoppolo wasn't thinking about Trey Lance coming into the game. He was too busy using his own legs to convert first downs.
— Los Angeles Rams quarterback Matthew Stafford refused to let a sore right thumb derail his Sunday plans.
Items.vs: Indianapolis Colts vs. Los Angeles Rams

Items.description: — Through two games, quarterback Sam Darnold is thriving in Carolina.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: — Another Buffalo-Miami game, another lopsided Bills victory. And this one might wind up hurting the Dolphins more than most of the others.

— Arizona's Jordan Hicks didn't dare turn around as Minnesota's potential game-winning field goal floated toward the uprights. Instead, he watched the videoboard for a moment and then locked eyes with Ezekial Turner, who had been knocked to the turf,...
— It's good to be 2-0 with a franchise-best 10-game winning streak and an even more impressive run of nine straight 30-plus point performances in a victory.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: — Derrick Henry and the Tennessee Titans found a way to silence Seattle's notorious noise that hadn't been heard for nearly two years.
— Throughout his rehab from a broken ankle last season, Dak Prescott thought about what it would feel like to be on the field again and lead the Dallas Cowboys on a game-winning drive.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Chargers vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: — With a vault and a jump pass, and all the confidence from his coach and teammates he could ask for, Lamar Jackson finally beat Patrick Mahomes and Kansas City.
Items.vs: Baltimore Ravens vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: — While celebrating one of his four touchdowns, Aaron Jones lost a necklace he wears with a little black football containing some of the ashes of his late father.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Detroit Lions

Items.description: — The Houston Texans got a solid performance from rookie quarterback Davis Mills in his first career start Thursday night.
— Justin Tucker ended the game as if he was starting it, backing up an extra step or two and kicking the football with every bit of force he had in his right foot.
— Josh Allen will never forget the emotional support Bills offensive coordinator Brian Daboll provided the quarterback following the loss of his grandmother 13 months ago.
— It's not enough to talk about changing the culture, something Zac Taylor started doing the moment he took over as Cincinnati Bengals head coach more than two years ago.
— After three games and a lot of ugly football, Arthur Smith finally picked up his first win as an NFL coach and his first game ball, courtesy of Matt Ryan.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: — Byron Murphy caught a glimpse of J.J. Watt bearing down on Trevor Lawrence and figured the pass would be underthrown.
— The Tennessee Titans know it's almost impossible to win a game turning the ball over three times.
— Only one brand of football comes to mind when Jameis Winston thinks about the best New Orleans Saints teams of the past.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: — Justin Fields had nowhere to run or hide. Passing was strictly prohibited.

— The Chargers had just turned the Kansas City Chiefs over for the fourth time Sunday. Los Angeles coach Brandon Staley was left with a crucial fourth-down call with less than a minute left in a tie game.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Los Angeles Chargers

Items.description: — The Las Vegas Raiders are off to their best start since 2002.
Items.vs: Las Vegas Raiders vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: — Vic Fangio has a rejoinder ready for anyone downplaying Denver’s first 3-0 start in five years just because the Broncos' opponents are a combined 0-9.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. New York Jets

Items.description: — After two narrow losses to start the season, Kirk Cousins and the Minnesota Vikings found a foolproof way to avoid the type of harrowing finish that has haunted them more often than not.
— Sean McVay's excitement over the big-play potential the Los Angeles Rams have with Matthew Stafford finally got the best of him Sunday.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Rams vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: — With only seconds to play and no timeouts, Aaron Rodgers had no doubt where he'd look to drive the Green Bay Packers to a game-winning kick.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: — Dak Prescott ran toward the tunnel, raising his arms to the fans and tossing them souvenirs after the Dallas Cowboys manhandled the Philadelphia Eagles in prime time.
— Robert Saleh had just gotten soaked from a celebratory Gatorade bath when he turned to Zach Wilson after earning their first NFL victory together.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description: — Ezekiel Elliott and the Dallas Cowboys ran over the NFL's No. 1 defense, answering a little history from the legs of Carolina quarterback Sam Darnold.

— Daniel Jones and the indefatigable New York Giants faced down deafening crowd noise in the Superdome, erased an 11-point deficit in the fourth quarter and broke into the win column in a game fittingly decided on the final play.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. New York Giants

Items.description: — After winning the NFL's Coach of the Year award in his first season with Cleveland, Kevin Stefanski now has a victory over his old team in Minnesota to highlight the start of his second year.
— Justin Fields took some inspiration from Russell Wilson and flashed the skills that made him the No. 11 overall pick in the draft.
— With a flair for improvisation, Taylor Heinicke has been pulling off these sort of bizarre plays most of his life.

— The last seven times Carson Wentz had played in a football game, he had walked off on the losing side. His final four appearances with Philadelphia last season, all losses. His first three appearances with Indianapolis this season, all losses.
— Patrick Mahomes, Tyreek Hill and the Kansas City Chiefs gave Andy Reid a record-setting homecoming.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: — Defensive end Jerry Hughes and the Buffalo Bills' defense made it clear from the beginning.
— In every quarter of a dominant victory on the Rams' home turf, Kyler Murray and the Arizona Cardinals confirmed they're no longer the annual afterthought in the NFC West.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Rams vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description: — Russell Wilson spun away from a sack and delivered a perfect strike for another TD pass.
— Lamar Jackson won this one with his right arm. He used his quick feet to crown Baltimore's 23-7 thumping of the Denver Broncos and tie an NFL rushing record.
— Randall Cobb demonstrated why Aaron Rodgers wanted the veteran receiver back in Green Bay.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Pittsburgh Steelers

Items.description: — Tom Brady brought two decades of touchdown passes, victories and championships to New England.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers
Los Angeles Chargers vs. Las Vegas Raiders

Items.description: — Matthew Stafford was able to manage the discomfort with the finger on his throwing hand and pick apart the Seattle Seahawks' beleaguered defense.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. Los Angeles Rams
Atlanta Falcons vs. New York Jets

Items.description: — Jalen Hurts was quiet in the run game for the better part of three quarters, often handing off on zone-read options instead of keeping the ball.
— Mike Zimmer has seen enough game-deciding kicks in eight years as coach of the Minnesota Vikings, with outcomes more often than not favoring the other team, that he usually turns away.
— Ben Roethlisberger and the Pittsburgh Steelers silenced the noise. At least for a week.
— Derrick Henry enjoyed another happy homecoming while continuing to torment his hometown team.

— Antonio Brown is 33 years old and no longer the top playmaker on his team. With Tom Brady's help on and off the field, though, the oft-troubled receiver is making the most of an opportunity to revive his career with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: — After Jameis Winston connected with Marquez Callaway on a Hail Mary touchdown on the final play of the first half, Sean Payton recalled a similar play in his first season as New Orleans Saints coach.
— Green Bay Packers kicker Mason Crosby fell into a nightmarish Sunday as the afternoon grew late and a stiff wind kept the flag billowing right to left in Paul Brown Stadium.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: — Trailing on the road in the fourth quarter, the New England Patriots needed Mac Jones to deliver on Sunday.
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: — Justin Herbert and the Los Angeles Chargers showed early in the season they can rally to win close games on the road.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Chargers vs. Cleveland Browns

Items.description: — Justin Fields hyperextended his left leg and got the wind knocked out of him on a tackle in the second quarter. Although Chicago's rookie quarterback was seriously shaken up, he walked to the sideline and only stayed there for two plays before...
Items.vs: Las Vegas Raiders vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: — Zach Allen will enjoy his postgame trip to Shake Shack after an exhausting, physical win over the San Francisco 49ers. He and the rest of the Arizona Cardinals' defense certainly deserve a burger or two.
— Dak Prescott celebrated until the end with more than 90,000 fans in his home stadium for a third consecutive week — and third straight win for the rolling Dallas Cowboys.
Items.vs: Dallas Cowboys vs. New York Giants

Items.description: — Bills quarterback Josh Allen scrambled to the left on the mushy turf in Arrowhead Stadium, saw the Chiefs defensive back go low for the tackle and made like an Olympian by leaping over him for a first down.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: — Even more than usual, the Baltimore Ravens needed Lamar Jackson to do pretty much everything as they tried to climb out of a second-half hole.
